 {"id":"ultrasearch-c00.9.1","content_hash":"06ef9cb546d7caa22aef57fd1450abbcd631e2e786736ea54b2e0d90f6edc88e","title":"Feature gating for advanced modules","description":"Add config/feature flags to toggle advanced features independently, ensuring baseline behavior unchanged when disabled.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:30:24.153455384Z","updated_at":"2025-11-20T23:30:24.153455384Z","source_repo":".","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.9.1","depends_on_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:34:28.855706931Z","created_by":"daemon"}],"comments":[{"id":5,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.9.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Status 2025-11-20: feature-gating framework will wrap advanced modules; awaiting baseline workspace and core features. Plan: config-driven feature flags with defaults off, compile-time cargo features where appropriate; integrate with config reload.","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:43:43Z"},{"id":12,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.9.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Config reference adds feature flags section (all default false) for advanced modules: multi-tier index, delta index, adaptive scheduler, doc-type analyzers, semantic search, plugin system, log dataset mode, mem_opt_tuning, auto_tuning. Validation to enforce combinations (e.g., delta -\u003e multi_tier).","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:46:38Z"},{"id":20,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.9.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Holding advanced/feature flags work until c00.1.2 workspace editions fixed; config surface already documented and implemented. No code changes needed right now.","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:54:49Z"},{"id":26,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.9.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Awaiting base workspace/service stabilization before adding connective code for feature gating (config flags already defined/documented).","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:57:20Z"}]}
